# Content Strategy

## Content Types and Organization

### Blog Posts

Blog posts should be organized in a structured way:

```
/content/blog/
├── developer/             # Developer-focused blog posts
│   ├── technical-posts/   # Highly technical content
│   ├── tutorials/         # Step-by-step guides
│   └── career/            # Career development posts
├── tattoo/                # Tattoo artist blog posts
│   ├── designs/           # Posts about tattoo designs
│   ├── techniques/        # Posts about tattooing techniques
│   ├── stories/           # Client stories and experiences
│   └── industry/          # Tattoo industry insights
└── personal/              # Personal life and combined interests
```

Blog post frontmatter structure:

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
slug: "post-slug"
description: "Brief description for SEO and previews"
date: "2023-07-15"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
category: "categoryName"
image: "/images/blog/post-featured-image.jpg"
alt: "Description of the featured image"
author: "Allison"
draft: false
seo:
  title: "SEO-optimized title (if different from post title)"
  description: "SEO-optimized description"
  ogImage: "/images/blog/og-image.jpg"
---
```

### Portfolio Projects

Developer projects should be structured as:

```
/content/projects/
├── featured/              # Highlighted projects (shown first)
└── archive/               # Older or less prominent projects
```

Project frontmatter structure:

```yaml
---
title: "Project Name"
slug: "project-slug"
description: "Brief description of the project"
date: "2023-06-10"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
