## Content Creation Guidelines

### Writing Style

#### Developer Content
- Professional but approachable tone
- Clear and concise language
- Technical accuracy is paramount
- Use code examples where appropriate
- Include diagrams for complex concepts
- Link to references and additional resources

#### Tattoo Content
- Artistic and expressive language
- Focus on visual descriptions
- Discuss techniques and artistic choices
- Share stories and inspiration
- Be respectful of clients and their stories
- Highlight the meaning behind designs

### SEO Best Practices

- Use descriptive, keyword-rich titles
- Include meta descriptions for all content
- Use semantic HTML structure
- Optimize images with descriptive filenames and alt text
- Use heading hierarchy appropriately (H1, H2, H3)
- Include internal links to related content
- Ensure content is original and valuable
- Aim for comprehensive coverage of topics
- Update older content regularly
- Use canonical URLs to avoid duplicate content

### Image Guidelines

- Use high-quality images (min 1200px wide for featured images)
- Compress images for web (WebP format preferred)
- Provide multiple sizes for responsive design
- Always include meaningful alt text
- Use descriptive filenames (e.g., pink-traditional-rose-tattoo.webp)
- Consider adding watermarks to tattoo artwork
- Obtain permission before posting client photos
- Credit other artists if sharing their work
- Maintain consistent aspect ratios when possible
- Use image captions to provide context

## Content Management Workflow

1. **Content Planning**
   - Identify audience needs and interests
   - Research keywords and topics
   - Create a content calendar
   - Define content goals and metrics

2. **Content Creation**
   - Draft content in Markdown
   - Select/create supporting images
   - Apply appropriate frontmatter
   - Review for accuracy and clarity

3. **Content Review**
   - Check for technical accuracy
   - Proofread for grammar and spelling
   - Ensure consistent style and tone
   - Verify all links work properly

4. **Content Publishing**
   - Add to appropriate content directory
   - Set publication date
   - Test appearance on site
   - Verify SEO elements

5. **Content Promotion**
   - Share on social media
   - Notify email subscribers
   - Engage with community responses
   - Monitor performance

6. **Content Maintenance**
   - Regularly audit for outdated information
   - Update with new developments
   - Refresh images and examples
   - Optimize based on performance data

## Content Performance Metrics

Track the following metrics to evaluate content effectiveness:

- Page views and unique visitors
- Time on page
- Bounce rate
- Conversion rate (newsletter signups, contact form submissions)
- Social shares
- Comments and engagement
- Backlinks
- Search ranking positions
- Click-through rate from search results

## Accessibility Considerations

- Provide transcripts for audio content
- Add captions to videos
- Use sufficient color contrast
- Avoid conveying meaning through color alone
- Use descriptive link text
- Provide alternative text for images
- Use semantic HTML structure
- Ensure keyboard navigability
- Test with screen readers
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards

## Legal and Ethical Guidelines

- Only use images you own or have rights to use
- Get written permission before sharing client stories
- Respect copyright and fair use
- Provide proper attribution
- Clearly disclose affiliate relationships
- Protect client privacy
- Be transparent about sponsored content
- Include appropriate disclaimers
- Follow industry ethical standards
- Obtain model releases for recognizable people in photos 